description: This header file defines the API interface for an SNMP plugin in the Advanced Networking Service Container (ANSC) platform. It declares functions related to initialization, support checks, unloading, and memory management for the plugin.

methods.name: COSA_Init
methods.description: Initializes the SNMP plugin with a maximum supported version and plugin info handle.

methods.name: COSA_Async_Init
methods.description: Performs asynchronous initialization of the SNMP plugin.

methods.name: COSA_IsObjectSupported
methods.description: Checks if a given object is supported by the plugin.

methods.name: COSA_Unload
methods.description: Unloads the plugin and performs cleanup.

methods.name: COSA_MemoryCheck
methods.description: Checks plugin memory usage or leaks.

methods.name: COSA_MemoryUsage
methods.description: Reports current memory usage of the plugin.

methods.name: COSA_MemoryTable
methods.description: Displays or manages memory table information for the plugin.
